    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3353544704" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer331045436522113260">★✰✰✰✰ - Did Not Finish<br/>I tried. I really tried.<br/>The back cover was promising something amazing: in an alternative future, they start using old concentration camps for reality shows. People chosen randomly are the prisoners while others are the guards whose mission is basically to mistreat the prisoners. <br/>Yet, this book was really bad: the fact it&apos;s a short book was a problem here because I wasn&apos;t even concerned about what happened to the characters. We don&apos;t learn to know them, don&apos;t learn to love </span>
  <span id="freeText331045436522113260" style="display:none">★✰✰✰✰ - Did Not Finish<br />I tried. I really tried.<br />The back cover was promising something amazing: in an alternative future, they start using old concentration camps for reality shows. People chosen randomly are the prisoners while others are the guards whose mission is basically to mistreat the prisoners. <br />Yet, this book was really bad: the fact it's a short book was a problem here because I wasn't even concerned about what happened to the characters. We don't learn to know them, don't learn to love them so we just don't give à f*ck to what can happen to them. <br />There isn't a single character that was developed. <br />The style is a nightmare: short sentences, sometimes complex vocabulary used for absolutely no reason, no detailed description of what's happening. All this leads to an incredibly bad book. I didn't even finish it because my reading was so boring and painful (yeah, I didn't even finish a 120-page book). <br />I usually love <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/40416.Am_lie_Nothomb" title="Amélie Nothomb" rel="nofollow noopener">Amélie Nothomb</a>'s books, I think they're always so well-written and interesting. This one is sadly a big <b> NO </b> for me. Don't read it. Don't trust the catchy back cover. </span>
  <a data-text-id="331045436522113260" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


