<div id="review_3933724231" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3933724231" />
    <a title="Rose " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/105842983-rose"><img alt="Rose " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1598077004p2/105842983.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3933724231?book_show_action=true">Jun 09, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rose " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rose " href="/user/show/105842983-rose">Rose </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780571234929" href="/book/show/933790.Sulphuric_Acid">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3933724231" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4129667295343104987">&quot;Concentration&quot; is a reality show with a simple bunch of rules: there are prisoners and guards, the last ones can show merciless to the first without a defined explanation and whoever isn&apos;t in conditions to advance will be immediately executed. Nevertheless, the Nazi-style line of the novel has their own powerful meanings and remarks in a very cohesive way the cruelty and absence of boundaries in our daily society. <br/><br/>However, for me there were some many lost opportunities to a better development, </span>
  <span id="freeText4129667295343104987" style="display:none">"Concentration" is a reality show with a simple bunch of rules: there are prisoners and guards, the last ones can show merciless to the first without a defined explanation and whoever isn't in conditions to advance will be immediately executed. Nevertheless, the Nazi-style line of the novel has their own powerful meanings and remarks in a very cohesive way the cruelty and absence of boundaries in our daily society. <br /><br />However, for me there were some many lost opportunities to a better development, because the tittle and the blurb were simply amazing, and I was just not waiting the story of a stereotypical young woman with a unique name who was constantly pretending to be God and its respective counterpart.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4129667295343104987" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
