              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27498480-stephanienicole?shelf=bought-2018">bought-2018</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27498480-stephanienicole?shelf=dystopian">dystopian</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27498480-stephanienicole?shelf=the-reading-rush">the-reading-rush</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2287898940" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer654379499273965987">This translated short work describes a dystopian near-future where people are randomly grabbed off the streets and forced into concentration camps until their deaths - all to be filmed and viewed on television. The two main characters are a woman prisoner who becomes the &quot;star&quot; of the show and the role model / de facto leader of her fellow prisoners and a guard who becomes obsessed with her. With current media events showing protesters being grabbed off the streets of Portland by secret police, </span>
  <span id="freeText654379499273965987" style="display:none">This translated short work describes a dystopian near-future where people are randomly grabbed off the streets and forced into concentration camps until their deaths - all to be filmed and viewed on television. The two main characters are a woman prisoner who becomes the "star" of the show and the role model / de facto leader of her fellow prisoners and a guard who becomes obsessed with her. With current media events showing protesters being grabbed off the streets of Portland by secret police, this book is hauntingly prescient.<br /><br />My favorite scene was a discussion between the prisoners debating who is the most evil: the guards who physically beat them, the show's producers, or the politicians who allow it? It is the viewers who watch evil and do nothing.</span>
  <a data-text-id="654379499273965987" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


