    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2262619502" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3674742570237358435">Excellent. A disturbing story of citizens forced into a concentration camp for reality tv. Both the camp &amp; the public seeing it as entertainment are horrifying. But Nothomb has a wonderful dry wit &amp; draws strong, memorable characters. Moving tension between guard Zdena &amp; Pannonique, the viewers’ favourite prisoner. Explores loss of identity, how low we will go for ‘entertainment’, apathy &amp; the mob mentality. A great novella. <br/><br/>This is third Amelie Nothomb book (after Petronille and Fear and Trembl</span>
  <span id="freeText3674742570237358435" style="display:none">Excellent. A disturbing story of citizens forced into a concentration camp for reality tv. Both the camp &amp; the public seeing it as entertainment are horrifying. But Nothomb has a wonderful dry wit &amp; draws strong, memorable characters. Moving tension between guard Zdena &amp; Pannonique, the viewers’ favourite prisoner. Explores loss of identity, how low we will go for ‘entertainment’, apathy &amp; the mob mentality. A great novella. <br /><br />This is third Amelie Nothomb book (after Petronille and Fear and Trembling) - all have been great reads - varied but equally strong. I’m wondering if she’s underrated as I don’t hear many people (In aust, UK, USA) talk about her? Or it could be just my ignorance. ;) </span>
  <a data-text-id="3674742570237358435" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


